1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,333
welcome back

2
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:05,700
today we are going to adventure in the mystical world of the UV tier quests

3
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:08,933
last time we rushed a UV Energy hatch

4
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:12,800
but we didn't complete any quest that wasn't strictly necessary

5
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:16,100
so today we are going to fix that

6
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,433
the main issue is that

7
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,666
those parts require a lot of motors

8
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:21,666
that contain a lot of americium

9
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:24,633
right now our only source of that material

10
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:26,800
is a single fusion reactor Mark 2

11
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:30,500
which can allow for a motor worth of material every half hour

12
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,433
we could make a second reactor to double the speed

13
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:36,666
but that would use up a lot of precious materials

14
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:41,033
also making americium in that way requires lutetium

15
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:42,733
and the way we are making it is

16
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:44,900
as waste of our nuclear reactors

17
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:49,600
which make a total of about 800 pieces every 10 hours

18
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:50,400
and so far

19
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:56,666
we have already used about one third of what we had stocked up since when our plant started its operation

20
00:00:56,866 --> 00:00:59,333
there are other ways of making lutetium

21
00:00:59,333 --> 00:00:59,533
but

22
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:03,000
I think we should just aim at the better way of making americium

23
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,200
fusion Mark 3

24
00:01:04,466 --> 00:01:06,866
so going back to our quest

25
00:01:06,866 --> 00:01:09,400
I think we are just going to wait a little bit more 

26
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:12,500
to stock up the materials to do that quest

27
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:13,900
in the meantime

28
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:16,166
we can do some other quest

29
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:17,033
such as Kevlar

30
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:20,733
Kevlar is the next tier of plastic which will be required later on

31
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:23,800
and is made by a chain of a lot of machines

32
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:26,533
and in the four hours it took to build that thing

33
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:31,933
we managed to also craft the motors required to complete the UV components quest

34
00:01:31,933 --> 00:01:33,800
next we need an assembler

35
00:01:33,866 --> 00:01:36,633
but we now use the overvolted multi block one

36
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:40,866
now we have to show the energy hatches we already made last time

37
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,233
we could craft some more in advance

38
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:45,133
or we can just borrow one

39
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,900
next we can borrow our water purification plant

40
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,866
and with that

41
00:01:49,866 --> 00:01:53,166
I think we can now move on to the fun parts of this mod pack

42
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:57,900
we are now going to start working with computation and glass fibers

43
00:01:57,900 --> 00:02:00,100
starting from a quantum computer

44
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:02,200
which you can see built here

45
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:06,000
its size can be increased to have up to 24 racks

46
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,800
but for now 6 will be enough

47
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:11,800
other than the usual maintenance issues

48
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,033
this machine will also have uncertainty issues

49
00:02:15,866 --> 00:02:17,433
to fix those issues

50
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:19,866
we have to use an uncertainty resolver

51
00:02:19,866 --> 00:02:24,233
where we will have to balance the bleeping intensity of some squares in a grid

52
00:02:25,033 --> 00:02:28,000
next we have to give power to that machine

53
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:31,033
it will need one UV amp of power for every rack

54
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,400
and one amp for the computer itself

55
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,833
that is 7 UV amps which is 28 zpm amps

56
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:42,700
so we use a 64 amps zpm hatch

57
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,800
once we connect the power lines

58
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,700
we can turn on our computer

59
00:02:48,066 --> 00:02:51,633
however it looks like it is still unable to compute

60
00:02:51,866 --> 00:02:56,300
and that is because we didn't insert any processor inside its racks

61
00:02:56,733 --> 00:02:59,733
once we insert a vent and a bunch of processors

62
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:00,866
we turn it on

63
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:04,733
and here we can see how much computation we are producing

64
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:06,500
and the processor's temperature

65
00:03:07,266 --> 00:03:10,666
and at some point something weird happened

66
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,833
our CPUs somehow melted

67
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:19,233
and it looks like something has indeed changed on how you should set up this machine

68
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,066
for the moment

69
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:22,600
we are not going to thinker with overclocks

70
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,600
so we just figure out something that works

71
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:29,500
we shall start with one vent and one crystal processor mainframe

72
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,633
the heat rapidly raises

73
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:35,333
but the hotter it gets the better the vent works

74
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:36,066
however

75
00:03:36,066 --> 00:03:38,466
we used only half of the rack spaces 

76
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:40,300
when we are paying for the full rack

77
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:44,200
so let's fill it up with the new better vents and one more main frame

78
00:03:44,466 --> 00:03:45,666
after some time

79
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:51,266
it looks like the temperature stabilized close to the maximum temperature for those processors

80
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,533
and we are not even using the best cooling system

81
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:56,633
we could try for a better setup

82
00:03:56,633 --> 00:04:00,066
but we are generating enough computation for the moment

83
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,666
also nowadays

84
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:05,300
the computer uses 1/4 of the power it used to eat

85
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:08,933
anyways we are now producing computation

86
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,233
but it is being wasted

87
00:04:10,233 --> 00:04:13,133
since nothing is connected to the optical connector

88
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:18,233
so time to work on the first machine that will put that computation to good use

89
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,900
the research station

90
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:20,666
to use it

91
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:23,433
we place a data stick inside the controller

92
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:26,900
and the item we want to research inside the object holder

93
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:27,700
and now

94
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:30,700
we just have to wait for the research to be completed

95
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:36,466
and the research we are doing is going to take quite a lot of computation and power

96
00:04:36,466 --> 00:04:38,733
but after a long wait

97
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:41,200
we managed to complete our research

98
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:44,266
we take that data to the assembly line databank

99
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,066
so that we can craft the new item we just unlocked

100
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:51,500
but while that new component is quite useful

101
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:54,400
it is not really helping us do any progress

102
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,200
we were going to work on Mark 3 fusion

103
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,866
but the correct way is probably

104
00:04:58,866 --> 00:05:01,866
to start doing some advanced biochemistry

105
00:05:02,066 --> 00:05:04,400
we start by making a new chain of machinery

106
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,833
to produce some Agar

107
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,933
and one other chain to produce some bio chaff

108
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:12,666
and to get all the plant, meat and bone required

109
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,466
we use some fishing ports

110
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,666
now that we have the materials

111
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:20,733
we can start brewing some random bacteria out of those things

112
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,600
we move into the clean room with those mundane bacteria

113
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,533
where using a bio lab

114
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:31,733
we start separating inside some petri dishes different variety of bacteria

115
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:34,200
now to use those cultures

116
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:37,666
we will want to place the petri dishes inside a bacterial vat

117
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:39,900
to make the bacteria multiply

118
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:43,833
a bacterial vat is a multi block with two main mechanics

119
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:45,600
to work at the best efficiency

120
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:50,333
you want to keep under check the bacteria population and the radiation levels

121
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:54,000
since we want to make lot of bacteria at low cost

122
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,200
we will want to make vats with wall shared radio hatches

123
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:01,800
the other mechanic is that we will want to keep the output hatch half filled

124
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,300
to maximize the bacteria growth

125
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:07,200
to do that we will have a cover that

126
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,833
once the hatch reaches half of the capacity

127
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:14,400
will turn on a pump to extract the new bacteria that is now in excess

128
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,300
and to quickly set up all of the vats

129
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:19,966
we can use a cover copy/paste tool

130
00:06:19,966 --> 00:06:22,100
and with the base completed

131
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:25,600
we can also build the rest of the multi vat structure

132
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,300
one other issue is that

133
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:32,066
to keep the radiation level constant in the vat during the bacteria growth

134
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:35,033
we will be consuming up radioactive material

135
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,700
for this stage we are using bismuth

136
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:41,300
which lasts 3 minutes and we have in huge amounts

137
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:43,733
however for later stages

138
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:46,033
we will be using stuff such as an naquadria

139
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:47,900
which only lasts 8 seconds

140
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:51,066
and is a material we will not want to waste

141
00:06:51,466 --> 00:06:55,033
so to avoid wasting radioactive materials

142
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:57,900
we are going to only input the radioactive stuff

143
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:03,200
when all of the other hatches are filled with the material required for the bacteria growth

144
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:07,400
and with later stages that will also grow in size

145
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,833
while the materials will get more expensive

146
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,733
and thus more easily depleted

147
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:14,466
and now that everything is ready

148
00:07:14,466 --> 00:07:17,000
we can start cultivating bacteria

149
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:17,800
initially

150
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,733
they will have to spread out just from the petri dish

151
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:24,100
but once they start growing inside the machine

152
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,533
the more we have the faster they will grow

153
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:31,466
until the space inside the machine will start becoming too much populated

154
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:34,000
and before they start starving

155
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,733
the Redstone circuit will trigger the pump to extract the excess 

156
00:07:38,133 --> 00:07:39,566
and the next stage will be

157
00:07:39,566 --> 00:07:44,466
to feed those normal bacteria with other stuff to the over evolutionized bacteria

158
00:07:44,466 --> 00:07:47,733
which will then produce raw growth catalyst medium

159
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:51,633
but those bacteria is a really slow one to grow

160
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:53,833
so to make it grow faster

161
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:59,033
we are going to momentarily replace the machine hatch with a smaller one to stock up some fluid

162
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,033
that we will replace into the bigger hatch 

163
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:02,833
for more fine regulation

164
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:04,400
and with that

165
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,633
we have the fluid required to produce stem cells

166
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:13,300
which we scan to obtain the instructions on how to build a neural processing unit

167
00:08:13,866 --> 00:08:17,100
meanwhile using a lot of expensive materials

168
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:21,866
we can also start preparing some circuit boards capable of hosting life

169
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,733
which are also part of the neural processing boards

170
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:29,400
now since we are going to need a lot of those

171
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,000
to speed up the process

172
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,933
we can use a dedicated advanced assembly line

173
00:08:34,466 --> 00:08:36,600
which is basically an assembly line

174
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:40,500
that will start a crafting before it has even finished the previous one

175
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:44,233
then we move to a new set of circuit assembly line

176
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:47,033
where we build our new wetware circuits

177
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,400
and here the research station comes into play

178
00:08:50,433 --> 00:08:53,533
since it is required to craft the wetware mainframe

179
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:57,666
and this was one way faster research than last time

180
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,466
and with that

181
00:08:59,466 --> 00:09:02,200
we can start building our new tier of circuits

182
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:05,800
the wetware main frames which are UHV tier

183
00:09:06,266 --> 00:09:09,933
and we will use those right away to make UV field generaters

184
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,133
for the fusion reactor Mark 3

185
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,300
but once again

186
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:17,533
we have been stopped by the speed of our Mark 2 reactor

187
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:21,266
so we have to find something else to do while we wait

188
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:24,900
we shall start by preparing the americium wafers

189
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:27,333
those take just a pinch of americium

190
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,866
but the cooking time is extremely high

191
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:34,666
one other thing we can do is gather some mysterious crystal rich stone

192
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:37,200
and this is the actual mining speed

193
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:41,133
of our new adamantium alloy hammer and quantum legging running speed

194
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:44,466
next we can go fight some bosses

195
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:47,400
such as the sequel of the Ender Dragon

196
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:50,833
which will drop some stuff that might be useful later on

197
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:55,300
and it looks like harvesting that stuff caused some weird thing to happen

198
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,100
then after disrupting this island

199
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,400
we can run away

200
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,866
all the way to Pluto

201
00:10:00,866 --> 00:10:03,733
where we fail at trying to tame a space dog

202
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:07,333
whom was hiding some rocket schematic in his nest

203
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:10,733
this time we are going to scan this schematic

204
00:10:10,866 --> 00:10:13,533
this will yield a way of creating copies of it

205
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:16,433
since we are going to need a couple more later on

206
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:17,666
in the meantime

207
00:10:17,666 --> 00:10:19,600
our americium boule is ready

208
00:10:19,633 --> 00:10:25,466
thus, we can cut it using the water that survived absolute zero and helium plasma temperatures

209
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:27,500
and we are going to use those wafers

210
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,666
to slowly make quantum power integrated circuits

211
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:33,400
which are required for the upcoming reactor

212
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,466
which now misses only one thing to be completed

213
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,400
americium

214
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,433
while waiting for it

215
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:42,233
we can build a couple of PCB factories

216
00:10:42,566 --> 00:10:46,433
those will make circuit boards cheaper and quicker than an LCR

217
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:51,533
or at least they will when we will equip the overclock and parallelization upgrades

218
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,400
for now

219
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:56,833
it will run on 22 EU per tick while on ZPM voltage

220
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:01,266
also we can even get bonus outputs at the cost of speed

221
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:04,133
and that's why we have a second PCB factory

222
00:11:04,133 --> 00:11:06,400
for the more expensive circuits

223
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:09,266
but that is something we will really notice only

224
00:11:09,266 --> 00:11:12,633
once we will be doing Bioware circuits in the next tier

225
00:11:12,866 --> 00:11:13,633
and now

226
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:16,266
while waiting for the remainder of the americium

227
00:11:16,266 --> 00:11:18,933
we can appreciate a couple of sunsets

228
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,933
but that didn't help us much

229
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:32,600
so I guess it is time to give up our indium

230
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:35,333
and do what we should have done one episode ago

231
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,833
a second fusion reactor Mark 2

232
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:41,900
now instead of taking an unbearable amount of time

233
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:44,600
it will only take a really really long time

234
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:48,266
so we can go watch some more sunsets

235
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:52,266
and after a long the wait

236
00:11:52,266 --> 00:11:55,266
we have finally completed our new fusion reactor

237
00:11:55,666 --> 00:12:00,266
which will start making americium in greater amounts as soon as it's charged up

238
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,000
however this recipe has a small issue

239
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:06,500
we are not getting americium but americium plasma

240
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:07,900
to get americium

241
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:11,800
we could either use a vacuum freezer which will use power

242
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,900
a heat exchanger which is a hassle

243
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,933
or we can run the plasma through a multi block turbine

244
00:12:17,933 --> 00:12:20,433
which will produce americium as waste

245
00:12:20,733 --> 00:12:24,533
however americium plasma has a huge energy density

246
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:27,300
meaning that the conversion will be rather slow

247
00:12:27,866 --> 00:12:31,133
unless we use a huge turbine with a huge flow

248
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:34,200
but we are still limited by the dynamo hatch

249
00:12:34,933 --> 00:12:35,500
anyways

250
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,300
what did we learn in today episode

251
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:43,800
yes we must always burn a lot of thorium in nuclear reactors during the early game

252
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,900
so we won't get stuck by lack of lutetium

253
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,000
and with that

254
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,533
I think we can close the episode

255
00:12:50,533 --> 00:12:51,100
bye bye

256
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,333
欢迎回来！

257
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:05,700
今天我们要去 UV 电压的神秘世界探索一番

258
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:08,933
上一集速通了 UV 能源仓

259
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:12,800
但没有完成非必要的任务

260
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:16,100
所以今天我们要解决这个问题

261
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,433
主要问题是

262
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,666
这些零件需要大量的马达

263
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:21,666
也就是大量的镅

264
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:24,633
现在唯一的镅来源

265
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:26,800
是单个聚变反应堆 Mk-II

266
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:30,500
它每半小时产出一个马达的量

267
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,433
我们可以再来一个使速度加倍

268
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:36,666
但那会消耗很多珍贵的材料

269
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:41,033
用这种方式制造镅也需要镥

270
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:42,733
而我们获得它的方式

271
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:44,900
是作为核反应堆的副产

272
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:49,600
每 10 小时大约 800 个

273
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:50,400
到目前为止

274
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:56,666
已经用了开机以来差不多三分之一的库存

275
00:00:56,866 --> 00:00:59,333
还有其他的方法来制造镥

276
00:00:59,333 --> 00:00:59,533
但是

277
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:03,000
使用更好的方式来制作镅才是焦点所在

278
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,200
也就是聚变反应堆 Mk-III

279
00:01:04,466 --> 00:01:06,866
所以回到任务

280
00:01:06,866 --> 00:01:09,400
我想得再等一会儿

281
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:12,500
来准备好任务所需的材料

282
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:13,900
同时

283
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:16,166
可以做一些其他的任务

284
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:17,033
比如凯夫拉线

285
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:20,733
凯夫拉是之后会用到的下一级塑料

286
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:23,800
需要一长串的机器来制作

287
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:26,533
在造它的四个小时里

288
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:31,933
我们做出了完成 UV 组件任务所需的马达

289
00:01:31,933 --> 00:01:33,800
接下来需要一台组装机

290
00:01:33,866 --> 00:01:36,633
我们已经在用升压的多方块组装机了

291
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:40,866
现在只要把做过的能源仓拿出来秀秀

292
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,233
我们可以再多做一些

293
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:45,133
或者是借一个

294
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,900
接下来我们借用净水厂

295
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,866
有了这个

296
00:01:49,866 --> 00:01:53,166
我想可以开始享受这个整合包有趣的部分了

297
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:57,900
研究算力和玻璃纤维

298
00:01:57,900 --> 00:02:00,100
从量子计算机开始

299
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:02,200
把它建在这

300
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:06,000
它的尺寸可以增加到最多 24 个机箱

301
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,800
但现在 6 个就足够了

302
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:11,800
除了通常的维护问题

303
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,033
这台机器也会有不确定性问题

304
00:02:15,866 --> 00:02:17,433
来解决这些问题

305
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:19,866
我们必须使用未定元解析器

306
00:02:19,866 --> 00:02:24,233
通过平衡网格中方格的哔哔声强度

307
00:02:25,033 --> 00:02:28,000
接下来给这台机器供电

308
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:31,033
每个机箱需要 1A UV

309
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,400
还有 1A UV 用于计算机本身

310
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,833
即 7A UV，28A ZPM

311
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:42,700
所以我们直接使用 64A ZPM 能源仓

312
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,800
一旦我们接上电

313
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,700
启动计算机试试

314
00:02:48,066 --> 00:02:51,633
看起来它仍然无法计算

315
00:02:51,866 --> 00:02:56,300
那是因为我们没有给机箱放入处理器

316
00:02:56,733 --> 00:02:59,733
一旦插入散热器和处理器

317
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:00,866
开启它

318
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:04,733
这里可以看到产生了多少算力

319
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:06,500
以及处理器的热量

320
00:03:07,266 --> 00:03:10,666
在某个时候发生了一些奇怪的事情

321
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,833
我们的 CPU 不知为何融化了

322
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:19,233
似乎现在配置这台机器的方式变了

323
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,066
暂时

324
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:22,600
我们不考虑超频

325
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,600
所以只需想好怎么让它工作

326
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:29,500
我们从一个散热片和一个晶体处理器主机开始

327
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,633
热量迅速上升

328
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:35,333
但越热散热片工作效率越高

329
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:36,066
然而

330
00:03:36,066 --> 00:03:38,466
机箱的空间只使用了一半

331
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:40,300
而我们已经造了整个机箱

332
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:44,200
所以再加一个散热片和处理器

333
00:03:44,466 --> 00:03:45,666
过了一段时间

334
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:51,266
看起来温度稳定在处理器可接受的最高温度了

335
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,533
我们甚至没有使用最好的冷却系统

336
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:56,633
我们可以尝试更好的设置

337
00:03:56,633 --> 00:04:00,066
但现在算力足够了

338
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,666
现在

339
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:05,300
计算机仅用了供给的四分之一电量

340
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:08,933
无论如何，我们现在正在产生算力

341
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,233
但它被浪费了

342
00:04:10,233 --> 00:04:13,133
因为没有任何东西连接到光学接口

343
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:18,300
所以是时候造出利用该算力的第一台机器

344
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,900
研究站

345
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:20,666
使用它

346
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:23,433
我们在控制器内放一个闪存

347
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:26,900
以及在物品固定支架上放待研究物

348
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:27,700
而现在

349
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:30,700
我们只需要等待研究完成

350
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:36,466
我们正在做的研究需要大量算力和电量

351
00:04:36,466 --> 00:04:38,733
经过漫长的等待

352
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:41,200
我们完成了研究

353
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:44,266
我们把数据放到装配线的数据库里

354
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,066
这样就可以制作刚刚解锁的新物品

355
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:51,500
虽然这个新组件非常有用

356
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:54,400
它并不会真正帮助我们取得任何进展

357
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,200
我们本来要研究聚变 Mk-III 的

358
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,866
但正确的路径可能是

359
00:04:58,866 --> 00:05:01,866
开始做一些高级生物化学

360
00:05:02,066 --> 00:05:04,400
我们从制造新的机器开始

361
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,833
生产一些琼脂

362
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,933
另一条产线产生糠

363
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:12,666
为了得到所需的植物、肉和骨头

364
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,466
我们用一下珠海渔场

365
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,666
现在我们有了材料

366
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:20,733
可以用这些东西培养出一些杂菌

367
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,600
把这些平凡的细菌搬入超净间

368
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,533
在那儿使用生物实验室

369
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:31,733
在培养皿中分离不同种类的细菌

370
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:34,200
要使用这些培养基

371
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:37,666
需要把培养皿放在培养缸里

372
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:39,900
使细菌繁殖

373
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:43,833
细菌培养缸有两个主要机制

374
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:45,600
才能以最佳效率工作

375
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:50,333
就是控制细菌数量和辐射水平

376
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:54,000
因为我们想以低成本大量制造细菌

377
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,200
我们使用共用放射仓的培养缸

378
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:01,800
另一个机制是我们希望保持输出仓半满

379
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,300
来最大化细菌生长

380
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:07,200
为此，我们使用一个覆盖板

381
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,833
一旦仓室达到半满

382
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:14,400
将打开泵来提取过量的新细菌

383
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,300
为了快速完成所有培养缸的配置

384
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:19,966
我们可以使用覆盖版复制/粘贴工具

385
00:06:19,966 --> 00:06:22,100
随着培养缸的底座完成

386
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:25,600
我们补全它的其他部分

387
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,300
另一个问题是

388
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:32,066
要在细菌生长过程中保持缸内辐射水平恒定

389
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:35,033
我们会耗尽放射性物质

390
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,700
在这个阶段，我们使用铋

391
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:41,300
它不仅存量充足，提供时间也长达三分钟

392
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:43,733
但是对于后期

393
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:46,033
我们将使用硅岩之类的东西

394
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:47,900
它只能持续 8 秒

395
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:51,066
并且是我们不想浪费的材料

396
00:06:51,466 --> 00:06:55,033
所以为了避免浪费放射性物质

397
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:57,900
我们将只在其他输入仓都存满了材料

398
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:03,200
再输入放射性材料

399
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:07,400
在后期，产线规模会变大

400
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,833
虽然材料会变得更贵

401
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,733
却也会更容易耗尽

402
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:14,466
现在一切都准备好了

403
00:07:14,466 --> 00:07:17,000
我们可以开始培养细菌

404
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:17,800
最初

405
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,733
它们需要从培养皿中扩散

406
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:24,100
一旦它们开始在机器内部生长

407
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,533
细菌有的越多，繁殖得越快

408
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:31,466
直到机器内部的空间变得过于拥挤

409
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:34,000
在他们开始挨饿之前

410
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,733
红石电路会触发泵来抽取多余细菌

411
00:07:38,133 --> 00:07:39,566
下一阶段将是

412
00:07:39,566 --> 00:07:44,466
把那些正常的细菌和其他东西一起喂给进化过度的细菌

413
00:07:44,466 --> 00:07:47,733
这将产生原始生长催化剂培养基

414
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:51,633
但是这些细菌的繁殖速度很慢

415
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:53,833
为了让它繁殖得更快

416
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:59,033
我们先用一个 LV 输入仓来存储液体

417
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,033
再替换成更大的输入仓

418
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:02,833
进行更精细的监控

419
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:04,400
有了这个

420
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,633
我们有了制造干细胞所需的液体

421
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:13,300
扫描它，获取制作神经处理单元的研究成果

422
00:08:13,866 --> 00:08:17,100
同时，使用大量昂贵的材料

423
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:21,866
我们开始准备能够承载生命的电路板

424
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,733
它们也是神经处理器的一部分

425
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:29,400
既然我们需要很多这样的东西

426
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,000
为了加快这个过程

427
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,933
我们可以使用专用的进阶装配线

428
00:08:34,466 --> 00:08:36,600
它的本质上和装配线没两样

429
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:40,500
但它会在完成上一次制作前开始下一次制作

430
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:44,233
然后我们做了一套新的电路装配线

431
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:47,033
来制作湿件电路

432
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,400
在这里，研究站开始发挥作用

433
00:08:50,433 --> 00:08:53,533
因为需要它来制作湿件主机

434
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:57,666
这是比上次更快的研究

435
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,466
有了这个

436
00:08:59,466 --> 00:09:02,200
我们可以开始建造新一级电路板了

437
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:05,800
UHV 等级的湿件处理器主机

438
00:09:06,266 --> 00:09:09,933
火速投产，制作 UV 力场发生器

439
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,133
用于聚变反应堆 Mk-III

440
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,300
但是再一次

441
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:17,533
聚变 Mk-II 的速度在拖我们后腿

442
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:21,266
所以我们在等待的时候找点别的事做

443
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:24,900
从准备镅掺杂的晶圆开始

444
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:27,333
它只需要一点点镅

445
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,866
但处理时间极长

446
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:34,666
另一件可做的事情是收集些神秘水晶

447
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:37,200
这是目前的采矿速度

448
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:41,133
这就是精金合金板和量子护腿给我带来的自信

449
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:44,466
接下来我们可以去打几个 boss

450
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:47,400
比如混沌守卫

451
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:50,833
它们将掉一些未来有用的材料

452
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:55,300
看来击杀这个 boss 导致了一些奇怪的事情发生

453
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,100
在破坏了这个岛之后

454
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,400
我们脚底抹油

455
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,866
一路到达冥王星

456
00:10:00,866 --> 00:10:03,733
我们在这驯服太空狗失败

457
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:07,333
它在地牢里藏了张火箭设计图

458
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:10,733
这次我们要扫描这个示意图

459
00:10:10,866 --> 00:10:13,533
这将产生一种创建它的副本的方法

460
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:16,433
因为我们不仅仅只需要一份图纸

461
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:17,666
同时

462
00:10:17,666 --> 00:10:19,600
我们的镅掺杂的单晶硅准备好了

463
00:10:19,633 --> 00:10:25,466
为此，我们可以用五级水来切割它

464
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:27,500
我们将使用这些晶圆

465
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,666
慢慢做量子功率集成电路

466
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:33,400
这是即将到来的反应堆所必需的

467
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,466
现在只剩下一件要完成的事情

468
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,400
镅

469
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,433
在等待的时候

470
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:42,233
我们可以建几个 PCB 工厂

471
00:10:42,566 --> 00:10:46,433
这将使生产电路板比起大化反时的大大降价

472
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:51,533
至少是在它能超频和并行时

473
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,400
暂时的

474
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:56,833
它将在 ZPM 电压下以 22 EU/t 运行

475
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:01,266
我们甚至可以以速度为代价获得额外的输出

476
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:04,133
这就是第二个 PCB 工厂的用途

477
00:11:04,133 --> 00:11:06,400
用来制备更昂贵的电路板

478
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:09,266
但它仅仅会在

479
00:11:09,266 --> 00:11:12,633
我们在下一阶段做生物电路板时有影响

480
00:11:12,866 --> 00:11:13,633
而现在

481
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:16,266
在等待剩余的镅时

482
00:11:16,266 --> 00:11:18,933
我们可以欣赏几场日落

483
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,933
但那对我们帮助不大

484
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:32,600
所以我想是时候放弃我们的铟了

485
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:35,333
做我们一集前就该做的事

486
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,833
做第二个聚变反应堆 Mk-II

487
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:41,900
现在与其花费无法忍受的时间

488
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:44,600
只需要很长很长的时间

489
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:48,266
我们可以去欣赏更多的日落了

490
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:52,266
经过漫长的等待

491
00:11:52,266 --> 00:11:55,266
我们终于完成了新的聚变反应堆

492
00:11:55,666 --> 00:12:00,266
一旦完成充能，它就会开始大量制造镅

493
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,000
但是这个配方有一个小问题

494
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:06,500
我们得到的不是镅而是镅等离子体

495
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:07,900
为了得到镅

496
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:11,800
我们要么消耗电力通入真空冷冻机来制备

497
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,900
或者用略显麻烦的热交换机

498
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,933
或者让等离子体通过多方块涡轮

499
00:12:17,933 --> 00:12:20,433
将镅以副产形式输出

500
00:12:20,733 --> 00:12:24,533
然而镅等离子体具有巨大的能量密度

501
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:27,300
这意味着转换会相当慢

502
00:12:27,866 --> 00:12:31,133
除非我们用巨大流量的巨大涡轮

503
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:34,200
但我们还是受到动力仓的限制

504
00:12:34,933 --> 00:12:35,500
不管怎样

505
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,300
我们在这一集中学到了什么？

506
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:43,800
在游戏初期必须烧大量的钍燃料棒

507
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,900
这样我们就不会因为缺少镥而陷入困境

508
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,000
有了这个

509
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,533
我想我们可以结束这一集了

510
00:12:50,533 --> 00:12:51,100
拜拜

511
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:40,500
（拥有更多并行）

